SIMPLE: declining
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: declining
<hw>declining</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>decreasing; <as>as,
steadily <ex>declining</ex> incomes</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> down(prenominal).</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>going from better to worse.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> deteriorating, failing, regressing, retrograde,
retrogressive.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>becoming less or smaller; <as>as, <ex>declining</ex>
powers of body and mind</as>. Opposite of
<ant>increasing</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> eroding.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>drawing to an end; waning; <as>as, his
<ex>declining</ex> years</as>.</def> <mark>[prenominal]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Declinometer</ent>⟦br⟧
